====================

   This opens the MUI about window.


@EndNode

@Node "Quit" "MiamiSpeedMeter.guide/Quit"
@Next "Settings..."
@Prev "About MUI..."
@Toc "Usage"

Quit menu entry
===============

   This will quit the program. Oh, you guessed that?

   If you try to quit Miami, MiamiSpeedMeter will be stopped by Miami,
so you don't have to quit it yourself.

   Shortcut: RAmiga+q


@EndNode

@Node "Settings..." "MiamiSpeedMeter.guide/Settings..."
@Next "MUI settings..."
@Prev "Quit"
@Toc "Usage"

Settings menu entry
===================

   This will open the settings window. There you can change the
interface, the refresh delay and whether average cps, byte count and
reset button should be displayed.


@EndNode

