@Prev "Settings..."
@Toc "Usage"

MUI settings menu entry
=======================

   This will open MUI's prefs window.


@EndNode

@Node "ARexx" "MiamiSpeedMeter.guide/ARexx"
@Next "About Miami"
@Prev "Usage"
@Toc "Main"

ARexx port
**********

   MiamiSpeedMeter has an ARexx port as all MUI programs have if you
don't disable that feature. Its name is @{b}MIAMISPEEDMETER.1@{ub} for the first
running instance, @{b}MIAMISPEEDMETER.2@{ub} for the second and so on. You can
use all standard MUI ARexx commands on this port.

   Additionally there are these commands:

@{b}RESET@{ub}
     This does the same as the Reset menu entry (see @{"Reset" Link "Reset"})

@{b}GETINTERFACE@{ub}
     This sets the result variable to the name of the interface
     currently monitored.

@{b}SET INTERFACE/K,REFRESHDELAY=DELAY/K/N@{ub}
     Sets the interface to be monitored and the refresh delay to the
     given values.

@{b}GUI TINYWINDOW=TINY/S,NOAVERAGE=NOAVG/S,NOBYTECOUNT=NOBYTE/S,NORESETBUTTON=NORESET/S@{ub}
     Changes the window according to the arguments. The arguments are
     the same as the command line arguments (see @{"Starting" Link "Starting"}). The
     defaults are set to "display", so the command @{b}GUI@{ub} alone will
     switch average, byte count and reset button display to on.


@EndNode

@Node "About Miami" "MiamiSpeedMeter.guide/About Miami"
@Next "About MUI"
@Prev "ARexx"
